	</header>
	<aside>
		The perfect combination of mint and chocolate served healthy.
	</aside>
	<img onload="showimage('article001a');" id="article001a" class="img noshow" src="article001a.jpg" alt="Mint Chocolate Greeny"/>
	<img id="article001b" class="img noshow" src="article001b.jpg" alt="Mint Chocolate Greeny"/>
	<img id="article001c" class="img noshow" src="article001c.jpg" alt="Mint Chocolate Greeny"/>
	<section id="recipe" class="noshow">
		<p>
			As a child, I was allowed to eat cake once a year &#8211; on my
			birthday. 
			As such, the importance of getting the right birthday cake was
			tremendous, for it had an entire year's worth of expectation
			to live up to. 
		</p>
		<p>
			This is proven by the fact that I still remember today, the best
			birthday cake I ever had as a child &#8211; a Baskin' Robbins Mint
			Chocolate Chip icecream cake. 
			My 9th birthday thus set the standard for all consequent birthday
			cakes &#8211; yet no cake has ever lived up to it since. 
		</p>
		<table class="ingredients">
			<caption>Ingredients</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">amount</th>
					<th class="name">name</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1</td>
				<td class="unit">scoop</td>
				<td class="name">
					protein powder (I used Fitnessguru's One Whey
					mint chocolate isolate), <span
						class="altor">or</span>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount">1</td>
				<td class="alt unit">scoop</td>
				<td class="alt name">
					any chocolate-flavoured protein powder (optional)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1</td>
				<td class="unit">cup</td>
				<td class="name">unsweetened almond milk</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1/2</td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td class="name">frozen banana</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1/2</td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td class="name">ripe avocado</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">2</td>
				<td class="unit">handfulls</td>
				<td class="name">organic baby spinich</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1/2</td>
				<td class="unit">cup</td>
				<td class="name">fresh mint leaves, <span
						class="altor">or</span>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount">1-2</td>
				<td class="alt unit">drops</td>
				<td class="alt name">mint extract (optional)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1</td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">dark cacao nibs</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount"></td>
				<td class="alt unit"></td>
				<td class="alt name">ice (optional)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="alt amount"></td>
				<td class="alt unit"></td>
				<td class="alt name">Stevia (optional, for sweetness)</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>
			Endowed with the freedom that adulthood brings, I would be
			well within my rights to embark upon a gluttonous quest to find that perfect
			mint chocolate chip ice cream cake. 
			Thankfully, my vanity is what prevents me from doing so, and <span class="nm">Lila, Chop!</span> 
			inspired me to recreate my own mint chocolate chip ice cream
			experience in a guilt-free, clean, healthy and protein-rich maner.  
		</p>
		<table id="steps">
			<caption>Steps</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">time</th>
					<th>instruction</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1</td>
				<td class="unit">min</td>
				<td>blend all the ingredients in a high-speed blender until thick and creamy.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1</td>
				<td class="unit">min</td>
				<td>garnish with a fresh mint leaf and additional cacao
					nibs.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Serve cold, and enjoy!</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>
			This is a very filling smoothie. To make the recipe leaner, simply use less avocado, and
			replace the frozen banana with crushed ice. Remember, the creamier
			the consistency and the more frozen the smoothie is, the more it will taste like ice cream. 	
		</p>
